<dec f='remake/makeint.h' l='732'/>
<doc f='remake/makeint.h' l='725'>/* Some systems (like Solaris, PTX, etc.) do not support the SA_RESTART flag
   properly according to POSIX.  So, we try to wrap common system calls with
   checks for EINTR.  Note that there are still plenty of system calls that
   can fail with EINTR but this, reportedly, gets the vast majority of
   failure cases.  If you still experience failures you&apos;ll need to either get
   a system where SA_RESTART works, or you need to avoid -j.  */</doc>
<dec f='remake/make.h' l='558'/>
<doc f='remake/make.h' l='551'>/* Some systems (like Solaris, PTX, etc.) do not support the SA_RESTART flag
   properly according to POSIX.  So, we try to wrap common system calls with
   checks for EINTR.  Note that there are still plenty of system calls that
   can fail with EINTR but this, reportedly, gets the vast majority of
   failure cases.  If you still experience failures you&apos;ll need to either get
   a system where SA_RESTART works, or you need to avoid -j.  */</doc>
